cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SI. 

This paper presents a deep sequential model for parsing discourse dependency structures of multi-party dialogues, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the proposed model utilizes deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The model also involves predicting and constructing a discourse structure, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper mentions experiments and performance evaluation, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
